  #################################################################
 #
 #  Configuration-file for 'heater' data- decoding and logging to databases and
 #   supporting other interface with data (MQTT_IF / SPS_IF ...)
 #
 ## Naming conventions (only for readability, not for rrdtool) ##
 # T := Temperatur
 # V := Value
 # C := Counter
 ##
 # 'systempart'-name should match to the available systemcomponent.
 #   Upper- and lower-case with or without 'underline'-chars are allowed.
 #   The sqlite 'database-tables' are created with this names.
 #
 # 'shortname'-name is used as "nickname" in system and must have unique naming
 #   for the first three chars. Upper- and lower-case is allowed.
 #   This shortname (nickname) is used for internally mapping to the
 #   real  'systempart'-name.
 #
 # 'logitem'-name is used as GAUGE-value name for viewing and database-storing.
 #   Upper- and lower-case with or without 'underline'-chars are allowed.
 #   !!! namelength must be 1 to max 18 chars at least !!!
 #   The sqlite   'database-columns' and
 #   the rrdtool 'database-columns' are created with this names.
 #
 # Importent notice:
 #  The parameter 'shortname' and 'logitem' must not be changed after database -
 #  creation. Also 'logitem' is used decoder-internal and therefore must never
 #  be changed.
 ##########
 #
 # Different to above parameters the following parameter-contents are changeable.
 # Only the functionality of heater-system fixed the values of 'set_param' to
 # the possible setable limits.
 #
 # 'accessname'-name is used for accessing the decoded heater-data from external
 # requesting clients.
 # Choose this name as you like, keep in mind that it must be system unique
 #  and should have the systempart in it's name like: 'hc1_anyname'.
 # Also the commands to the heater-system are using this 'accessname'.
 #  But there are only a few commands setable and only this one's
 #  have that 'set_param' qualifier included.
 #
 # 'set_param' defines the valid setable parameter for a heater setup-command.
 # Depending on the logitem and it's functionality the set-parameter must have
 # diffenrent content.
 # The valid parameters depends also on the current heater-system
 # with its's currently running controller.
 # Particular the difference between the bussystems and the used telegrams make
 # there the limitation.
 # example:
 #   controller-type 'Fxyz' againsed 'Cxyz' make the difference in the
 #   usable commands like: 'heizen', 'sparen', 'frost' against 'comfort2' or 'eco'.
 #
 # The rules for building this set-parameter are:
 #     1. using strings, separated with ','.
 #     2. optional parameters can be separated with '|'.
 #     3. no white-spaces should be included.
 #     4. parameters are case-sensitive.
 #     5. One example and it's meaning is:
 #          <set_param>Tdesired,3,1,T,heizen|sparen|frost</set_param>
 #      5.1 short name                     := Tdesired
 #      5.2 amount of following parameters := 3
 #          The followers are the possible parameter, at least amount of two is required.
 #      5.3 parameter1: heater-circuit number in range 1...4.
 #      5.4 parameter2: a tag for the handling with it := T -> received parameter is used
 #           for temperatur.
 #      5.5 parameterN: optional more parameters if required, in this example it is:
 #           'heizen' or 'sparen' or 'frost'.
 #
 # Keep in mind that this is still under development and not yet everything will work
 # already.
 # My aim is to make it more general, but the manufacturer is very creative and make
 # this happen more complicated. But at least, we are the winner (I'll hope so :-)
 #
 ##
